{
  "stem": "3097.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Let's say about, maybe, 4 meters by, you know, by 3 meters by 2 meters.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At night, we used to go tear off those-- those signs, take them in the forest, and we had roofs-- OK, many places, because we had to move from place to place.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also what we used to do-- we took the-- we knew what-- we took the signs from here, put them over there, and those from over there, put them over here, so you confuse the people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't know where to go, the- the Germans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's what we did, you know-- for the joke of it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But mainly, we used to have the roof made out of the signs of the rail-- what the Germans put up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because we had the Poles against us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We have the-- the [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Endecs-- ?] you know, those people who were rabid anti-Semites-- also against us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They did actually cooperate with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were some groups in Poland of the-- they used to call them [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]-- the national-- national armed powers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They already cooperated in Germans-- with Germans against the Jews and maybe against the-- the left-linked Poles, too.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were Poles, actually, you see?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we had to-- really was squeezed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One of the guys who came to my group was a manufacturer of ladies' shoes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "During the war, beginning of the war, he had 200 pairs of shoes put in a false soffit or whatever in his apartment or whatever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He told this to Kozubek-- to one of my people, of the partisans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this Kozubek was greedy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He took a wagon-- a horse-drawn wagon-- and he went there to get those shoes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It so happened that the biggest murderer, [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Rumpel, ?] lived-- had a girlfriend in this building.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
